<TEXT>
presidentelect bush has turned for his defense 
secretary to a former senator who strongly backed the military 
buildup of the reagan years and worked as a consultant for major 
military contractors after leaving congress 
john tower a 63yearold texan retired from the senate in 1985 
after 24 years including a stint as chairman of the armed services 
committee 
after leaving the senate tower went into business as a defense 
consultant he also has served as an arms negotiator for president 
reagan and he headed the white houses irancontra investigative 
panel 
he was widely mentioned as a candidate for the defense department 
job by most accounts the only one he really wanted under reagan 
but reagan never made the move 
tower comes to the job now at a time when the pentagon faces 
acute budget pressures because of the federal budget deficit and the 
array of costly new weapons systems developed as part of the 
military buildup 
the bottom line is that we must provide at least as much if 
not more defense for less money tower said after bush announced 
his nomination friday 
the announcement followed a lengthy background check that brought 
a public airing of towers private life including an acrimonious 
divorce talk of drinking and womanizing and questions about the 
propriety of naming someone to the job who had worked with so many 
defense companies 
bush dismissed a lot of rumors that proved to be groundless 
and said i am totally satisfied in that regard 
the presidentelect apparently decided that towers extensive 
financial ties to weapons companies that he will do business with as 
defense secretary was not a bar to service 
asked if tower would stay out of defense department matters 
involving corporations for whom he has consulted bush said i 
expect so but i dont know i expect he would just like anybody 
coming in i think well bend over backward in that regard 
according to public records and associates towers consulting 
firm of tower and associates has been on annual retainer with the 
following defense contractors martinmarietta textron ltv 
aerospace and defense co rockwell international and british 
aerospace 
in addition towers firm received about 100000 a year under a 
contract for consulting services to hicks and associates a mclean 
vabased aerospace consulting firm headed by donald hicks a former 
undersecretary of defense 
through hicks firm tower indirectly provided advice to still 
more defense contractors 
towers firm received 96000 a year from ltv although other 
fees were not revealed an associate richard billmire acknowledged 
some were in the range of 100000 a year 
there are some retainers in the neighborhood of that figure 
and others that are substantially less billmire said 
tower also received income from speeches about 15000 each for 
the 30 or so a year he gives according to his agent joe cosby 
he has a second consulting firm dallasbased tower eggers and 
greene which is described as providing financial services and 
advice 
tower was a former board member of a dallas bank first republic 
with his dallas firm tower was part of a group that unsuccessfully 
bid to buy the financially troubled bank before it was taken over by 
north carolinabased ncnb corp 
billmire described towers work for the defense contractors as 
providing advice on the direction of future defense projects and 
advice and information on government budget processes including the 
transfer of money among projects 
hicks said he signed a contract for towers services in order to 
gain the benefit of his advice and opinions about what congress was 
likely to do on defense issues 
in the senate tower was a supporter of reagans strategic 
defense initiative and the mx missile but he was said to be angered 
by the administrations failure to agree on a missile deployment 
plan and he moved to block development until an acceptable plan was 
found 
tower left the arms negotiating post after 14 months and in late 
1986 reagan named him to head his irancontra investigative panel 
its report laid part of the blame for affair on reagans management 
style but had little to say about bushs involvement 
in naming tower bush was bringing a fellow texan to the upper 
levels of his administration tower was the first republican elected 
to the senate from texas since reconstruction he is a native of 
houston and was a college professor before running for the senate 
he was elected in 1961 in a special election to fill lyndon 
johnsons seat after johnson became vice president 
</TEXT>
