<TEXT>
as a former senator john tower will receive a 
certain deference at his confirmation hearing as george bushs new 
defense chief but he may also face serious questioning about his 
willingness to shoehorn pentagon spending into a newly limited 
budget 
i would say john tower will be accorded special respect but no 
special privilege said sen john warner rva the senior 
republican on the senate armed services committee 
warner told reporters he had consulted with committee chairman 
sam nunn dga and that hearings on towers nomination would 
probably take place the week of jan 20 he said while tower would 
undergo careful questioning he ultimately will be confirmed 
the day after the senate confirms him hell move into harness 
and step out warner said hell require no onthejob 
training 
nunn in a statement said the confirmation hearings would focus 
on towers plans for meeting defense challenges over the next four 
years including who will be appointed to senior pentagon jobs how 
congressionally mandated reforms will be put in place and how 
security will be maintained in a time of tight budgets 
some of those who will sit in judgment on tower when he goes 
before the committee were there when tower chaired the panel during 
the first four years of the reagan administration 
it will be a love feast predicted frank gaffney a former 
top pentagon official now at the center for security policy a 
conservative washington research organization 
hes tough hes shrewd hes smart said one of those former 
colleagues sen gordon humphrey rnh hes not likely to be 
hoodwinked by the soviets he is certainly well prepared in terms of 
expertise and experience 
one issue likely to emerge during the confirmation hearings is 
how the nomination of melvyn r paisley the former navy assistant 
secretary who is a central figure in the pentagon procurement 
scandal got past tower when he chaired the committee 
tower has said his panel never was given access to an fbi 
background report on paisley that contained damaging allegations and 
might have kept paisley from getting the senior job committee 
member sen carl levin dmich has asked president reagan to 
explain why those allegations never surfaced in 1981 when paisley 
was nominated 
the long fbi background check on tower and talk about bushs 
reported desire to put a strong manager in as towers 
secondincommand have weakened the new nominee said rep patricia 
schroeder dcolo she said that will make him more open to attack 
for coziness with the defense industry 
you have a new secretary who never saw a weapons system he 
didnt like schroeder a member of the house armed services 
committee told reporters he is tainted in being able to run a 
tough aggressive pentagon 
over his career this is not somebody who has staked out a 
reputation as a tough budgetcutting six guntoting decision 
maker said gordon adams defense director of the center on budget 
and policy priorities an independent analysis group 
in the early 1980s while chairman of the committee he signed 
off on the biggest peacetime buildup in defense since the end of 
world war ii he defended it he pushed it through adams said 
the mission today is very different he said its how do 
you get defense spending under control hes got to be a guy whos 
learned how to say no and ive not seen that in his past 
lawrence korb another former pentagon official now at the 
brookings institution a liberal research organization said tower 
will face a severe test the question is whether he will be able 
to put together the team that can take a 400 billion program and 
put it into a 300 billion budget korb said 
gaffney however said towers role should be to advocate 
pentagon spending and fight against cuts 
tower is not going to have to prove anything except that he has 
the wisdom and tenacity to minimize the damage done to national 
security by people trying to effect draconian cuts in the defense 
budget gaffney said 
