a navy f14 fighter jet crashed friday 
night while trying to land both crewmen escaped injury according 
to the us coast guard 
the aircraft went down in the alameda estuary a short distance 
before a runway at the northern end of the island housing the 
alameda naval air station 5 miles east of san francisco said coast 
guard lt michael sullivan 
one crewman was rescued by a passing tugboat and the other was 
picked up by a coast guard rescue boat 
the plane apparently sank 
both the pilot and the radar officer were taken to a naval 
hospital following the 7 pm accident sullivan said both were in 
very good condition and were being observed for possible effects 
of shock because they were in the water a short time before rescue 
it was not known whether either of the men were able to eject 
before the crash 
the f14 known as the tomcat is a twoseat carrierbased 
fighter 
