meet the grammrudman target 
the president also contended that his budget plan will do so 
without touching social security or raising taxes 
economic growth will increase revenues by 80 billion without 
new taxes just by holding spending increases to less than 80 
billion we will reduce the deficit and put ourselves on track for a 
balanced budget by 1993 reagan said 
bush has the option of scrapping reagans entire budget if he 
wants and submitting his won proposal after he takes office jan 20 
bush has declined to say whether he will submit his own plan but 
has said he wants to open negotiations with congress over ways to 
reduce the deficit 
as he has many times in during his two terms reagan used his 
fiveminute address to argue for an array of changes in the budget 
process many of them grant more power to the president rather to 
congress and have therefore met stiff opposition on capitol hill 
they include presidential authority to veto individual items in 
appropriations bills a constitutional amendment requiring a 
balanced budget and granting the president authority not to spend 
money that congress has appropriated among others 
congress must reform its faulty budget process and we need a 
balanced budget amendment to the constitution so that the federal 
government does not spend more than it takes in reagan said 
after i leave office next month i will campaign for these 
reforms so today im asking you to join me in this vital campaign 
for the future by making your voice heard if we achieve these 
reforms the deficit will be ancient history in no time reagan 
said 
