the energy department should be able to 
meet conditions set by three governors for resolving a deadlock over 
the storage of radioactive waste from nuclear weapons plants a 
department official said 
the governors of idaho colorado and new mexico emerged from a 
private meeting friday with pledges of cooperation from deputy 
energy secretary joseph salgado 
i think weve laid a solid groundwork for progress weve put a 
process in place i believe it will bear fruit salgado said 
but the governors said they would continue to pressure the 
government to make sure the energy department honors its promise to 
hasten the opening of the waste isolation pilot plant a prototype 
storage facility under construction near carlsbad nm 
